{"parse":{"title":"British Flying Training School Program","pageid":35871697,"revid":817244661,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>At the beginning of the <a href=\"/wiki/Second_World_War\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Second World War\">Second World War</a> the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">United Kingdom</a> recognised that it would need to train a large number of pilots. A number of flying and aircrew training schools were set up across the <a href=\"/wiki/British_Empire\" title=\"British Empire\">British Empire</a> where pilots could be trained without risk of enemy interference. The British Flying Training Schools (BFTS) were set up in the United States of America from 1941 as a result of the Lend Lease Bill.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RAFOAK_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RAFOAK-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Locations\">Locations</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=British_Flying_Training_School_Program&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Locations\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"noviewer thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:452px\"><div style=\"position:relative;width:450px;border:1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Usa_edcp_location_map.svg\" class=\"image\" title=\"British Flying Training School Program is located in the US\"><img alt=\"British Flying Training School Program is located in the US\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Usa_edcp_location_map.svg/450px-Usa_edcp_location_map.svg.png\" width=\"450\" height=\"279\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Usa_edcp_location_map.svg/675px-Usa_edcp_location_map.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Usa_edcp_location_map.svg/900px-Usa_edcp_location_map.svg.png 2x\" data-file-wid